  <li><p>You care for someone for 35 hours a week or more - for example, cooking meals, or helping them with their shopping</p>
</li>
  <li><p>The person you care for gets one of these disability benefits:</p>

    <div class="benefit-list">
      <ul class="list-bullet">
        <li><strong>Personal Independence Payment</strong> &mdash; the standard or enhanced rate of the Daily Living Component
        </li>
        <li><strong>Disability Living Allowance</strong> &mdash; the middle or highest rate</li>
    <li><strong>Attendance Allowance</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Constant Attendance Allowance</strong> &mdash; the Addition to Disablement Benefit at normal maximum rate or more, or the Addition to War Disablement Pension at full rate</li>
        <li><strong>Armed Forces Independence Payment</strong></li>
      </ul>

    </div></li>
</ol>

<hr>

